ns |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Martha Russ I||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was sunk in a British and Canadian air raid on [[Hamburg]].<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nanho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary submarine chaser was sunk by [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]] aircraft off Makassar.<ref name=\"ReferenceO\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_sc.htm |title=Auxiliary Sub Chasers of WWII, Converted Merchant Ships, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=21 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Stormarn||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was sunk in a British and Canadian air raid on Hamburg.<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==Unknown date==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=Unknown date 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[Type A Ko-hyoteki-class submarine|''Ha-69'']]\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass2-|Type C|midget submarine}} was scuttled at [[Davao Gulf|Davao]], Philippines in late March.<ref name=\"Japanese Submarines\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German seaplane tender|Hans Rolshoven||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The salvaged, but unrepaired, ''Hans Rolshoven''-class [[seaplane tender]] was bombed and sunk by British bombers at Sassnitz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_cv_hans_rolshoven.htm |title=Hans Rolshoven class Seaplane Tender, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Jersbek|1938|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk by Soviet aircraft on 9 March, or bombed and sunk by Soviet [[Douglas A-20 Havoc]] and [[Ilyushin Il-4]] 