295>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u296.html |title=U-296 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-758||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was severely damaged in a British air raid on [[Kiel]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]]. She was struck from the navy list on 16 March. Scrapped in 1946.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|YCF-23}}, {{USS|YCF-29}},<br>{{USS|YCF-36}} and {{USS|YCF-37}}\n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The non-self-propelled car floats were lost en route to [[Enewetak Atoll|Eniwetok]] sometime in March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.navy.mil/faqs/faq82-2.htm |title=Casualties, Navy & Coast Guard ships WWII |publisher=history.navy.mil |accessdate=8 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140410224418/http://www.history.navy.mil/FAQs/faq82-2.htm |archivedate=10 April 2014 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|20em}}\n\n{{shipevents|1945}}\n{{WWII shipwrecks}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of shipwrecks by year|1945-03]]\n[[Category:Maritime incidents in March 1945| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe '''list of shipwrecks in March 1945''' includes [[ship]]s sunk, foundered, grounded, or otherwise lost during [[March 1945]].\n{{dynamic list}}\n{{Calendar ToC}}\n==1 March==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=1 March 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese auxiliary gunboat|Chohakusan Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The auxiliary [[gunboat]] was sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] off [[Naha]], [[Okinawa]] by [[United States Navy]] aircraft.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_pg.htm |title=auxiliary gunboats of World War II |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese auxiliary patrol boat|Ch\u014dkai Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=The auxiliary guard ship was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceD\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/japan/jap_esc_aux_pc.htm |title=Auxiliary patrols and guard boats converted from fishing vessels in WWII, Japan |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=17 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Daishin Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy KATA-604: The transport was sunk in Kuji Bay, [[Amami \u014cshima]] by United States Navy aircraft from Task Force 38. Sixty passengers and two crewmen were killed.<ref name=\"Japanese Supply Ships\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Kenizaki_t.htm |title=Japanese Supply Ships |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Ship|Japanese oiler|Eisho Maru||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy HI-88G: The [[tank ship|oiler]] was bombed and sunk off Yulin, [[Hainan Island]]. Twenty-nine passengers and seven crewmen were killed.<ref name=\"Japanese Subchasers\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/CH-20_t.htm |title=Japanese Subchasers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=3 March 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Hannibal|AG-1|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The [[collier (ship type)|collier]] was bombed and sunk as a target in [[Chesapeake Bay]].\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Hoshi Maru No. 11||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy KATA-604: The transport (a.k.a. ''Juichei Maru'') was sunk in Kuji Bay, Amami \u014cshima by United States Navy aircraft from Task Force 38. Lost on board were 82 IJA Explosive Motor Boats.<ref name=\"Japanese Supply Ships\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Japanese supply ship|Kinezaki||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy KATA-604: The supply ship 