rmany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] near [[Hel, Poland|Hela]] ({{coord|54|25|N|18|50|E}}) with the loss of all 50 crew.<ref name=U367>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u367.htm |title=U-367 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=18 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|UIT-6||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The submarine was sunk in an Allied air raid on Monfalcone.<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German patrol boat|UJ-1105 Wilhelm Loh||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The naval trawler/submarine chaser was bombed and sunk by Allied aircraft in the [[Skagerrak]].<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5614856|shipname=Uj.1105 |accessdate=16 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==17 March==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=17 March 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Daffodil||2}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Landing Craft carrier hit a mine off [[Dieppe]] and sank the next morning. Nine crew were killed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.grieme.org/d-3/daffodil-2.html#histoire |title=Daffodil |publisher=www.grieme.org |accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Ellringon'' (or&nbsp;''Ellrington'')\n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=The 22-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|47.6|ft|m|1|adj=on}} [[fishing vessel]] was destroyed by fire at [[Cordova, Alaska|Cordova]], [[Territory of Alaska]].<ref name=alaskashipwreckse>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-e/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (E)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMCS|Guysborough|J52|6}} \n|flag={{navy|Canada|1911}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass-|Bangor|minesweeper}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Bay of Biscay]] by the [[submarine]] {{GS|U-868||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 51 