dian air raid on Hamburg.<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==Unknown date==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=Unknown date 1945 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=[[Type A Ko-hyoteki-class submarine|''Ha-69'']]\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The {{sclass2-|Type C|midget submarine}} was scuttled at [[Davao Gulf|Davao]], Philippines in late March.<ref name=\"Japanese Submarines\"/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German seaplane tender|Hans Rolshoven||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The salvaged, but unrepaired, ''Hans Rolshoven''-class [[seaplane tender]] was bombed and sunk by British bombers at Sassnitz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_cv_hans_rolshoven.htm |title=Hans Rolshoven class Seaplane Tender, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Jersbek|1938|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk by Soviet aircraft on 9 March, or bombed and sunk by Soviet [[Douglas A-20 Havoc]] and [[Ilyushin Il-4]] aircraft on 28 March, or struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the Baltic Sea off [[Pillau]], [[East Prussia]] on 30 March.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI |id=5614930 |shipname=Jersbek |accessdate=27 October 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceH\">{{cite web |url=http://wio.ru/fleet/sunk/baltic.htm |title=ships sunk in the Baltic by soviet aircraft |publisher=Rufleet |accessdate=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Kete|SS-369|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Balao|submarine}} was lost in the [[Pacific Ocean]] on or after 20 March. She may have been torpedoed and sunk on 20 March by {{Jsub|Ro-41||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}).<ref name=seekrieg194503/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item \n|ship={{HMS|LCA 1112}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The [[landing craft assault]] was lost sometime in March.<ref name=\"ReferenceQ\">{{cite web |url= http://www.navypedia.org/ships/uk/brit_aws_lcalcsm.htm |title=LCA Assault Landing Craft and LCS(M) Support Landing Craft, Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item \n|ship={{HMS|LCA 1153}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The [[landing craft assault]] was lost sometime in March.<ref name=\"ReferenceQ\">{{cite web |url= http://www.navypedia.org/ships/uk/brit_aws_lcalcsm.htm |title=LCA Assault Landing Craft and LCS(M) Support Landing Craft, Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|LCM 1011}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=The [[landing craft mechanized]] was lost in the [[Mediterranean Sea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/uk/brit_aws_lcm.htm |title=LCM) Landing Craft, Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Navalhistory.net\">{{cite web |url=http://www.naval-history.net/WW2BritishLossesbyDate3.htm |title=Royal Navy vessels lost at sea Jan. '44-Nov. 45 |publisher=Navalhistory.net |accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German torpedo boat|T40||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T41||2}} and {{ship|German torpedo boat|T42||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The incomplete Type 1941 torpedo boats were scuttled by their builder to prevent capture by the Red Army at the Schichau Yard, Elbing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_tb_1941.htm |title=Type 1941 Torpedo Boats, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German torpedo boat|T43||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T44||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T45||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T46||2}}, <br>{{ship|German torpedo boat|T47||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T48||2}}, {{ship|German torpedo boat|T49||2}}, and {{ship|German torpedo boat|T50||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II:The incomplete Type 1941 torpedo boats were destroyed by their builder to prevent capture by the Red Army at the Schichau Yard, Elbing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_tb_1941.htm |title=Type 1941 Torpedo Boats, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German minesweeper|TS 15||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The incomplete torpedo training ship, originally designed to be an [[M-class minesweeper (Germany)|M 1940-class minesweeper]], was destroyed on the stocks at Memel sometime in March (probably on 23 March).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=1940 Type Minesweepers, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-296||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was lost on or about 12 March on patrol in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] (approximately {{coord|55|30|N|7|00|W}}) possibly due to striking a [[naval mine|mine]]. All 42 crew were killed.<ref name=U295>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u296.html |title=U-296 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-758||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC]] [[submarine]] was severely damaged in a British air raid on [[Kiel]], [[Schleswig-Holstein]]. She was struck from the navy list on 16 March. Scrapped in 1946.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|YCF-23}}, {{USS|YCF-29}},<br>{{USS|YCF-36}} and {{USS|YCF-37}}\n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The non-self-propelled car floats were lost en route to [[Enewetak Atoll|Eniwetok]] sometime in March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.navy.mil/faqs/faq82-2.htm |title=Casualties, Navy & Coast Guard ships WWII |publisher=history.navy.mil |accessdate=8 March 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=http